🔹 Basic Methods

length() 
→ returns number of characters 
→ "Hello".length() = 5

charAt(i) 
→ returns character at index 
→ "Hello".charAt(1) = 'e'

toUpperCase()
→ converts to uppercase 
→ "hi".toUpperCase() = "HI"

toLowerCase() 
→ converts to lowercase 
→ "HI".toLowerCase() = "hi"

trim() 
→ removes leading & trailing spaces 
→ " hi ".trim() = "hi"

🔹 Comparison Methods

equals(s) 
→ checks if two strings are equal
→ "abc".equals("abc") = true

equalsIgnoreCase(s)
→ compares ignoring case 
→"abc".equalsIgnoreCase("ABC") = true

compareTo(s) 
→ compares lexicographically 
→ "abc".compareTo("abd") = negative

🔹 Searching Methods

contains(s) 
→ checks if substring exists
→ "hello".contains("ell") = true

indexOf(x) 
→ returns first position 
→ "hello".indexOf('l') = 2

lastIndexOf(x)
→ returns last position 
→ "hello".lastIndexOf('l') = 3

startsWith(s) 
→ checks beginning 
→ "hello".startsWith("he") = true

endsWith(s) 
→ checks ending 
→ "hello".endsWith("lo") = true

🔹 Modification Methods

substring(b) 
→ returns from index 
→ "hello".substring(2) = "llo"

substring(b,e) 
→ returns range 
→ "hello".substring(1,4) = "ell"

replace(a,b) 
→ replaces characters 
→ "hello".replace('l','x') = "hexxo"

replaceAll(r,x) 
→ replaces using regex 
→ "a1b2".replaceAll("\\d","") = "ab"

concat(s) 
→ joins strings 
→ "hi".concat(" all") = "hi all"

🔹 Conversion Methods

toCharArray() 
→ converts to char array 
→ "hi".toCharArray() = ['h','i']

valueOf(x) 
→ converts to string 
→ String.valueOf(10) = "10"

🔹 Checking Methods

isEmpty() 
→ checks if string is empty 
→ "".isEmpty() = true

isBlank() 
→ checks empty or spaces 
→ " ".isBlank() = true
